# --- harness dogfooding state (machine-specific) ---
# harness generates these from YOUR selection and personal shared library
# (~/.harness), so they are not portable across contributors. Run `harness`
# to regenerate them locally. See CONTRIBUTING.md.
/harness.yaml
/AGENTS.md

# --- Project-local agent artifacts ---
# Localized (vendored) artifacts under .agents/ ARE committed on purpose:
# localizing is how we standardize the artifacts every contributor works with
# (the go-code-standards rule, the low-level-design composition, the spec-driven
# skill, and the specs under .agents/specs/). Be mindful of third-party licenses
# before localizing something you are not free to redistribute.
#
# Only the generated entry point stays out of git (harness.yaml / AGENTS.md
# above): those mix in each maintainer's personal ~/.harness selections. Run
# `harness apply` to regenerate them locally. See CONTRIBUTING.md.
